ðŸ”¹ Step 1: Question: Aapko ek integer array nums diya gaya hai (positive, negative, aur zero numbers ho sakte hain). Aapko us subarray (continuous elements) ka maximum product nikalna hai.
Return karo maximum product.

ðŸ”¹ Step 2: Intuition (Question ka hidden twist)
Agar sirf positive numbers hote â†’ easy, saare multiply karke max nikal lete.
Problem aati hai negative numbers aur 0 ke wajah se:
Zero â†’ multiplication reset kar deta hai. (Kuch bhi Ã— 0 = 0)
Negative numbers â†’ 2 negative mil ke positive product banate hain.
Example: [-2, -3] â†’ product = 6 (jo max ho sakta hai).
Matlab kabhi negative bhi best answer de sakta hai.
ðŸ‘‰ Isliye hume dono track karna padega:
max product till now (because positive maximize karta hai),
min product till now (because ek aur negative mile toh min Ã— neg â†’ bada max ban sakta hai).

ðŸ”¹ Step 3: Algo Approach
maxProd aur minProd ko track karte raho for every index.
Current number num ke saath teen option compare karte hain:
sirf num (start new subarray),
num * maxProd (extend previous max),
num * minProd (extend previous min, ho sakta hai negative Ã— negative â†’ bada ban jaye).
Har step pe:
tempMax = max(num, num*maxProd, num*minProd)
tempMin = min(num, num*maxProd, num*minProd)
fir maxProd = tempMax, minProd = tempMin
Global answer me max store karte raho.

ðŸ”¹ Step 4: Dry Run
Example: nums = [2,3,-2,4]
Start:
maxProd = 2, minProd = 2, ans = 2
i = 1 (num = 3):
max option â†’ max(3, 3*2, 3*2) = max(3, 6, 6) = 6
min option â†’ min(3, 3*2, 3*2) = min(3, 6, 6) = 3
â†’ maxProd = 6, minProd = 3, ans = 6
i = 2 (num = -2):
max option â†’ max(-2, -2*6, -2*3) = max(-2, -12, -6) = -2
min option â†’ min(-2, -2*6, -2*3) = min(-2, -12, -6) = -12
â†’ maxProd = -2, minProd = -12, ans = 6
i = 3 (num = 4):
max option â†’ max(4, 4*-2, 4*-12) = max(4, -8, -48) = 4
min option â†’ min(4, 4*-2, 4*-12) = min(4, -8, -48) = -48
â†’ maxProd = 4, minProd = -48, ans = 6
âœ… Final ans = 6

ðŸ”¹ Step 5: Time & Space Complexity
Time: O(n) (ek pass me nikal lenge).
Space: O(1) (sirf kuch variables use ho rahe).
